exercises.name: Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: A fundamental upper body exercise that targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps. Lie on a flat bench and press the barbell from chest to full extension.
instructions: Lie flat on bench with feet on floor
Grip barbell slightly wider than shoulder width
Lower bar to mid-chest with control
Press bar up to starting position
tips: Keep your feet flat on the floor for stability
Maintain a slight arch in your lower back
Don't bounce the bar off your chest

exercises.name: Barbell Back Squat
exercises.description: The king of leg exercises. A compound movement that builds overall lower body strength and mass.
instructions: Descend by breaking at hips and knees
Lower until thighs are parallel or below
Drive through heels to return to start
tips: Keep your chest up and core braced throughout
Your knees should track over your toes
Don't let your knees cave inward

exercises.name: Conventional Deadlift
exercises.description: A total body strength builder that primarily targets the posterior chain. One of the most effective exercises for building overall strength.
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart, bar over mid-foot
Bend down and grip bar just outside legs
Keep back straight, chest up, core tight
Drive through heels, extending hips and knees
Stand fully upright, then lower with control
tips: Keep the bar close to your body throughout the lift
Maintain a neutral spine - don't round your back
Engage your lats by pulling the bar into your shins

exercises.name: Pull-Up
exercises.description: A bodyweight exercise that builds back width and pulling strength.
instructions: Hang from bar with overhand grip
Pull yourself up until chin over bar
tips: Pull with your elbows, not just your hands
Keep your shoulders down and back
If you can't do a full pull-up, use resistance bands or do negatives

exercises.name: Push-Up
exercises.description: A classic bodyweight exercise for building upper body pushing strength.
instructions: Lower body until chest near floor
tips: Don't let your hips sag or pike up
Keep your core tight throughout the movement
For easier variation, elevate your hands or do from knees

exercises.name: Plank
exercises.description: A fundamental core stability exercise that builds endurance in the abdominals and lower back.
instructions: Start in push-up position on forearms
tips: Focus on maintaining a neutral spine
Don't hold your breath - breathe normally
If your form breaks, rest and reset rather than continuing with poor form

exercises.name: Dumbbell Bicep Curl
exercises.description: An isolation exercise for building bicep size and strength.
instructions: Stand with dumbbells at sides, palms forward
tips: Don't swing or use momentum - keep it controlled
Keep your elbows pinned to your sides
Squeeze at the top for maximum contraction

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
exercises.description: An isolation exercise for building shoulder width by targeting the lateral deltoid.
tips: Lead with your elbows, not your hands
Don't go above shoulder height to avoid impingement
Use lighter weight and focus on form over ego

exercises.name: Goblet Squat
exercises.description: A beginner-friendly squat variation using a dumbbell or kettlebell held at chest level.
tips: This is a great exercise for learning proper squat form
The weight at your chest helps keep your torso upright
Use this to practice depth before moving to barbell squats

exercises.name: Walking Dumbbell Lunge
exercises.description: A unilateral leg exercise that builds strength and improves balance.
instructions: Push off front foot to step forward
tips: Take a long enough step to avoid knee strain
Keep your torso upright throughout the movement
Control the descent - don't crash down

exercises.name: Incline Barbell Bench Press
exercises.description: A chest press variation that emphasizes the upper chest and front deltoids.
instructions: Lie back and grip barbell slightly wider than shoulders
Unrack bar and lower to upper chest
Press bar up to full extension
tips: Don't set the incline too high or it becomes a shoulder exercise
Touch the bar to your upper chest, not your neck
Keep your feet firmly planted for stability

exercises.name: Incline Dumbbell Press
exercises.description: A dumbbell chest press on an incline bench for upper chest development.
instructions: Sit back with dumbbells at shoulder level
Lower with control to shoulder level
tips: Dumbbells allow for a greater range of motion than barbell
Don't let the dumbbells drift too far apart at the bottom
Control the weight on the way down

exercises.name: Dumbbell Chest Fly
exercises.description: An isolation exercise that stretches and contracts the chest muscles through a wide arc.
instructions: Lie flat on bench with dumbbells above chest
Lower dumbbells out to sides with slight elbow bend
Feel stretch in chest at bottom
Squeeze chest to bring dumbbells back together
Maintain the same elbow bend throughout
tips: Don't go too heavy - this is an isolation movement
Keep a slight bend in your elbows to protect the joint
Focus on the stretch and squeeze, not the weight

exercises.name: Cable Crossover
exercises.description: A cable exercise that provides constant tension throughout the chest fly movement.
instructions: Stand between cable stations with handles at high position
Pull handles down and together in front of chest
Squeeze chest at bottom of movement
tips: Lean slightly forward to emphasize the chest
Keep a slight bend in your elbows
Vary the cable height to target different parts of the chest

exercises.name: Chest Dip
exercises.description: A compound bodyweight exercise that targets the lower chest and triceps.
instructions: Grip parallel bars and lift yourself up
Lean forward slightly to emphasize chest
Descend until upper arms are parallel to floor
Push back up to starting position
tips: Lean forward to target chest more than triceps
Don't go too deep if you have shoulder issues
Add weight with a belt once bodyweight becomes easy

exercises.name: Lat Pulldown
exercises.description: A cable exercise that mimics the pull-up motion, great for building lat width.
instructions: Sit at lat pulldown machine with thighs secured
Grip bar slightly wider than shoulder width
Pull bar down to upper chest
tips: Don't lean too far back - slight lean is fine
Pull with your elbows, not your hands
Avoid pulling behind the neck

exercises.name: Barbell Bent-Over Row
exercises.description: A fundamental back exercise that builds thickness and strength in the upper back.
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart, grip barbell
Hinge at hips until torso is nearly parallel to floor
Pull bar to lower chest/upper abdomen
Squeeze shoulder blades together at top
tips: Keep your back straight throughout the movement
Don't use momentum to swing the weight
Pull to your belly button for more lat engagement

exercises.name: Dumbbell Row
exercises.description: A unilateral back exercise that allows for a greater range of motion.
instructions: Place one knee and hand on bench
Hold dumbbell in other hand, arm extended
Squeeze lat at top of movement
tips: Keep your back flat and parallel to the floor
Pull to your hip, not your armpit
Don't rotate your torso as you row

exercises.name: Seated Cable Row
exercises.description: A cable exercise that targets the middle back with constant tension.
instructions: Sit at cable row machine with feet on platform
tips: Keep your back straight - don't round forward
Avoid swinging your torso back and forth
Focus on pulling with your back, not your arms

exercises.name: Face Pull
exercises.description: A cable exercise that targets the rear deltoids and upper back for shoulder health.
instructions: Set cable at face height with rope attachment
Pull rope towards face, separating hands
Squeeze rear delts and upper back
tips: Pull to your face, not your chest
Externally rotate your shoulders at the end
This is a great exercise for posture and shoulder health

exercises.name: T-Bar Row
exercises.description: A row variation that allows for heavy loading and targets the middle back.
instructions: Straddle the T-bar with feet wide
Grip handle and hinge at hips
tips: Keep your back straight throughout
Don't round your lower back
You can use a close or wide grip for variety

exercises.name: Barbell Overhead Press
exercises.description: A fundamental shoulder exercise for building overhead pressing strength.
instructions: Stand with barbell at shoulder level
Grip slightly wider than shoulder width
tips: Keep your core braced to protect your lower back
Don't lean back excessively
Push your head through at the top

exercises.name: Dumbbell Shoulder Press
exercises.description: A seated or standing shoulder press using dumbbells for balanced development.
tips: Don't lock out aggressively at the top
Keep your back against the pad if seated
Control the weight on the way down

exercises.name: Dumbbell Front Raise
exercises.description: An isolation exercise targeting the front deltoids.
instructions: Stand with dumbbells in front of thighs
Raise one or both dumbbells to shoulder height
Keep arms straight with slight elbow bend
Alternate arms or do both together
tips: Don't swing the weight - use control
Stop at shoulder height
Use lighter weight and focus on the contraction

exercises.name: Rear Delt Fly
exercises.description: An isolation exercise for the rear deltoids, important for shoulder balance.
instructions: Bend over at hips or use incline bench
tips: Keep your torso stable - don't swing
Lead with your elbows, not your hands
Use lighter weight for better mind-muscle connection

exercises.name: Arnold Press
exercises.description: A shoulder press variation that rotates through the movement for complete deltoid activation.
instructions: Start with dumbbells at shoulder level, palms facing you
Press up while rotating palms to face forward
At top, palms should face away from you
Reverse the motion on the way down
tips: The rotation happens as you press, not before
Keep the movement smooth and controlled
This exercise hits all three deltoid heads

exercises.name: Barbell Shrug
exercises.description: An isolation exercise for building the trapezius muscles.
instructions: Stand holding barbell at thigh level
Shrug shoulders straight up towards ears
tips: Don't roll your shoulders - just go straight up and down
Hold at the top for a brief squeeze
Keep your neck neutral

exercises.name: Tricep Pushdown
exercises.description: A cable exercise that isolates the triceps for arm development.
instructions: Stand at cable machine with bar or rope attachment
Grip with palms down, elbows at sides
Push down until arms are straight
Return with control, keeping elbows fixed
tips: Keep your elbows pinned to your sides
Don't lean into the movement
Focus on the squeeze at the bottom

exercises.name: Overhead Tricep Extension
exercises.description: An isolation exercise that targets the long head of the triceps.
instructions: Hold dumbbell or cable overhead with both hands
Lower weight behind head by bending elbows
Extend arms back to starting position
tips: Keep your elbows close to your head
Don't let your elbows flare out
Control the weight on the way down

exercises.name: Skull Crusher
exercises.description: A lying tricep extension that effectively targets all three tricep heads.
instructions: Lie on bench with barbell or dumbbells extended over chest
Lower weight towards forehead by bending elbows
Keep upper arms perpendicular to floor
Extend arms back to starting position
tips: Lower to your forehead, not behind your head
Keep your elbows pointing up, not flaring out
Use an EZ bar for easier wrist positioning

exercises.name: Close-Grip Bench Press
exercises.description: A bench press variation that emphasizes the triceps.
instructions: Lie on bench and grip bar at shoulder width or narrower
Lower bar to lower chest with elbows tucked
Press bar back up to full extension
Keep elbows close to body throughout
tips: Hands about shoulder width apart
Keep elbows at 45 degrees or less
Don't go too narrow or you'll strain your wrists

exercises.name: Tricep Dip
exercises.description: A bodyweight exercise that targets the triceps using parallel bars or a bench.
instructions: Grip parallel bars and lift yourself up
Keep torso upright to emphasize triceps
Descend until upper arms are parallel to floor
Push back up to starting position
tips: Stay upright to keep focus on triceps
Don't go too deep if you have shoulder issues
For bench dips, keep feet on floor or elevated

exercises.name: Barbell Curl
exercises.description: A fundamental bicep exercise using a barbell for heavy loading.
instructions: Stand with barbell at thigh level, palms up
tips: Don't swing your body to lift the weight
Keep your elbows pinned to your sides
Use an EZ bar for easier wrist positioning

exercises.name: Hammer Curl
exercises.description: A curl variation that targets the brachialis and brachioradialis for arm thickness.
instructions: Stand with dumbbells at sides, palms facing in
Curl weights up keeping palms facing each other
tips: The neutral grip targets different muscles than regular curls
Don't swing the weight
You can curl both arms together or alternate

exercises.name: Preacher Curl
exercises.description: A bicep curl performed on a preacher bench for strict isolation.
instructions: Sit at preacher bench with upper arms on pad
Hold barbell or dumbbells with arms extended
tips: Don't come all the way down to avoid elbow strain
Keep your upper arms pressed against the pad
Control the negative portion

exercises.name: Cable Curl
exercises.description: A bicep curl using cables for constant tension throughout the movement.
instructions: Stand facing cable machine with handle at low position
tips: The cable provides constant tension unlike free weights
Try different attachments for variety
Stand far enough back for proper tension

exercises.name: Concentration Curl
exercises.description: A seated single-arm curl that isolates the bicep with strict form.
instructions: Sit on bench with legs spread
tips: This is a great exercise for mind-muscle connection
Don't swing - the position forces strict form
Focus on the peak contraction

exercises.name: Leg Press
exercises.description: A machine exercise for building quad, hamstring, and glute strength.
instructions: Sit in leg press machine with back against pad
Place feet shoulder-width apart on platform
Descend until knees are at 90 degrees
Press back up without locking knees
tips: Don't lock out your knees at the top
Keep your lower back pressed against the pad
Foot placement changes muscle emphasis

exercises.name: Leg Extension
exercises.description: An isolation exercise that targets the quadriceps.
tips: Don't use momentum - keep it controlled
Squeeze hard at the top
Don't go too heavy - this exercise can stress the knees

exercises.name: Lying Leg Curl
exercises.description: An isolation exercise that targets the hamstrings.
instructions: Lie face down on leg curl machine
tips: Don't lift your hips off the pad
Focus on the mind-muscle connection with your hamstrings
Control the negative portion

exercises.name: Romanian Deadlift
exercises.description: A hip-hinge movement that targets the hamstrings and glutes.
instructions: Stand with barbell at thigh level
Push hips back while lowering bar
Lower until you feel hamstring stretch
Drive hips forward to return to start
tips: Keep the bar close to your body
Don't round your back
Feel the stretch in your hamstrings at the bottom

exercises.name: Standing Calf Raise
exercises.description: An isolation exercise for building calf size and strength.
instructions: Stand on calf raise machine or step
Rise up on toes as high as possible
tips: Get a full stretch at the bottom
Pause briefly at the top
Keep your knees straight but not locked

exercises.name: Seated Calf Raise
exercises.description: A calf exercise that emphasizes the soleus muscle.
instructions: Sit in seated calf raise machine
Place balls of feet on platform
Raise heels as high as possible
tips: The bent knee position targets the soleus more
Use a full range of motion
Pause at the top for a better contraction

exercises.name: Hip Thrust
exercises.description: A glute-focused exercise that builds strength and size in the posterior chain.
instructions: Sit on ground with upper back against bench
Drive through heels to lift hips
tips: Keep your chin tucked throughout
Push through your heels, not your toes
Squeeze your glutes hard at the top

exercises.name: Bulgarian Split Squat
exercises.description: A single-leg squat variation that builds unilateral leg strength.
instructions: Stand in front of bench with one foot behind on bench
Drive through front foot to stand
tips: Keep your torso upright
Front shin should stay relatively vertical
Start with bodyweight before adding weight

exercises.name: Crunch
exercises.description: A fundamental core exercise that targets the rectus abdominis.
instructions: Lie on back with knees bent
Place hands behind head or across chest
tips: Don't pull on your neck
Focus on curling your ribcage towards your pelvis
Keep your lower back on the ground

exercises.name: Hanging Leg Raise
exercises.description: An advanced core exercise that targets the lower abs.
instructions: Hang from pull-up bar with arms straight
Keep legs straight or slightly bent
Raise legs until parallel to ground or higher
tips: Don't swing - use control
Focus on tilting your pelvis up
Bend knees to make it easier

exercises.name: Russian Twist
exercises.description: A rotational core exercise that targets the obliques.
instructions: Sit with knees bent, feet off ground or on ground
Lean back slightly, keeping back straight
Hold weight at chest or extend arms
Touch weight to ground on each side
tips: Keep your back straight - don't round
The rotation comes from your core, not your arms
Keep your feet off the ground for added difficulty

exercises.name: Dead Bug
exercises.description: A core stability exercise that teaches proper bracing.
instructions: Lie on back with arms extended up
Raise legs with knees bent at 90 degrees
Lower opposite arm and leg towards ground
Keep lower back pressed to floor
tips: Keep your lower back pressed into the ground
Move slowly and with control
This is great for teaching core stability

exercises.name: Mountain Climber
exercises.description: A dynamic core exercise that also elevates heart rate.
tips: Keep your hips down - don't pike up
Land on your toes
Go faster for more cardio, slower for more core focus

exercises.name: Cable Crunch
exercises.description: A weighted core exercise using cable resistance.
instructions: Kneel facing cable machine with rope at high position
tips: Focus on flexing your spine, not just bowing
Keep your hips stationary
This allows for progressive overload on abs

exercises.name: Bicycle Crunch
exercises.description: A dynamic crunch variation that targets both the rectus abdominis and obliques.
instructions: Lie on back with hands behind head
Bring one knee to chest while extending other leg
Rotate torso to bring opposite elbow to knee
tips: Don't pull on your neck
Focus on the rotation and elbow-to-knee connection
Keep your lower back pressed to the ground

exercises.name: Dumbbell Bench Press
exercises.description: A chest press using dumbbells for a greater range of motion and balanced development.
instructions: Lie on flat bench with dumbbells at chest level
Press dumbbells up until arms are extended
Lower dumbbells to sides of chest
Feel stretch in chest at bottom
tips: Dumbbells allow for a deeper stretch than barbell
Keep your shoulder blades retracted
Control the weight on the way down

exercises.name: Chin-Up
exercises.description: A pull-up variation with underhand grip that emphasizes the biceps.
instructions: Hang from bar with underhand grip
Pull yourself up until chin over bar
tips: The underhand grip makes this easier than pull-ups
Squeeze your biceps at the top
Don't swing - use controlled movement

exercises.name: Upright Row
exercises.description: A shoulder exercise that targets the lateral deltoids and traps.
instructions: Stand holding barbell or dumbbells at thighs
Pull weight up along body to chin level
Lead with elbows, keeping them above hands
tips: Don't go too heavy - this can stress the shoulders
Stop when elbows reach shoulder height
Use dumbbells if you have shoulder issues

exercises.name: Front Squat
exercises.description: A squat variation with the barbell in front, emphasizing the quads and core.
instructions: Rest barbell on front deltoids with clean grip or crossed arms
Descend by breaking at hips and knees
Keep elbows high and chest up
tips: Keep your elbows up throughout the movement
Stay more upright than back squat
Work on wrist mobility for the clean grip

exercises.name: Leg Raise
exercises.description: A core exercise performed lying down that targets the lower abs.
instructions: Lie on back with legs extended
Place hands under lower back for support
Raise legs until perpendicular to floor
Lower legs slowly without touching ground
tips: Keep your lower back pressed into the floor
Bend your knees to make it easier
Don't let your lower back arch off the ground

exercises.name: Reverse Lunge
exercises.description: A lunge variation stepping backward, easier on the knees.
instructions: Step one foot back into lunge position
Push through front foot to return
tips: Easier on the knees than forward lunges
Keep your torso upright
Step back far enough to maintain balance

exercises.name: Sumo Deadlift
exercises.description: A deadlift variation with wide stance that emphasizes the quads and adductors.
instructions: Stand with wide stance, toes pointed out
Grip bar between legs with arms straight
Push through legs while keeping chest up
tips: Push your knees out over your toes
Keep your chest up throughout
This variation is easier on the lower back

exercises.name: Hack Squat
exercises.description: A machine squat variation that targets the quadriceps.
instructions: Position yourself in hack squat machine
Place feet shoulder-width apart on platform
Push back up without locking knees
tips: The machine provides stability for heavy loading
Vary foot placement to target different muscles
Don't lock out your knees at the top
